.:: Puzzle 3x6-Level-3-4::.
There 6 different types of food: banana, cauliflower, cranberry, grapes, tomato, zucchini
6 different games are played: whist, mah-jongg, snooker, billiard, scrabble, bridge
City: rome, berlin, venice, paris, miami, hannover
 1. the person playing mah-jongg is the person traveling to venice##1
 2. the person playing snooker is on the left or right of the person eating banana##3
 3. the person playing whist is on the left of the person traveling to venice##1
 4. the person playing snooker is the person eating cranberry##1
 5. the person playing bridge is on the left or right of the person playing billiard##3
 6. the person playing billiard is the person traveling to paris##1
 7. the person eating tomato is on the left of the person traveling to rome##1
 8. the person eating zucchini is on the left or right of the person traveling to berlin##3
 9. the person eating cranberry is the person traveling to miami##1
10. the person playing bridge is on the left or right of the person traveling to berlin##3
11. the person traveling to berlin is on the left of the person playing mah-jongg##1
12. the person eating cauliflower is on the right of the person traveling to paris##1
13. the person playing billiard is on the far left or far right##3
14. the person traveling to miami is on the right of the person playing mah-jongg##1
15. the person traveling to hannover is on the left or right of the person eating cranberry##3

.:: Answer ::.
|         |     1      |      2      |   3    |    4     |     5     |    6    |
| Food    | tomato     | cauliflower | grapes | zucchini | cranberry | banana  |
| Game   | billiard  | bridge   | whist  | mah-jongg  | snooker   | scrabble |
| City     | paris | rome         | berlin | venice     | miami     | hannover  |

